            <ul class="bullet-list">
                <li><p><strong>3-IN-1 JACKETS</strong><br>Make skiing and snowboarding thrice as nice! Sport a 3-in-1 jacket that can be adjusted to the changing elements of the great outdoors. The outer jacket is water-resistant, while the inner jacket provides extra warmth. Depending on the conditions, these two jackets can be worn together as one or they can be worn separately. How do you keep from getting too hot while you&rsquo;re skiing or snowboarding? To prevent overheating, ensure that your 3-in-1 jacket has the latest breathable and insulation technologies, like PrimaLoft<sup>&reg;</sup> ThermoBall<sup>&trade;</sup> or Omni-Tech<sup>&trade;</sup>. What helps to keep the cold from entering your jacket? Make sure your jacket has an adjustable hood, plenty of drawstrings and Velcro<sup>&reg;</sup> tabs to block out frigid air. Stay warm and dry on the slopes in a 3-in-1 jacket from Columbia, The North Face or Marmot.</p></li>
                <li><p><strong>SKI PANTS</strong><br>How do you keep your bottom half dry when you&rsquo;re coming down the mountain? Slip into waterproof ski pants to keep you warm and cozy in the snow. How do you keep from overheating? Check out styles with venting systems for a comfortable feel. Look for pants with plenty of zip and cargo pockets to keep your valuables safe. You wouldn&rsquo;t want to loose your wallet, keys or phone out on the slopes. Want a perfect fit? Make sure you ski pants have belt loops and adjustable waist tabs. Get set for snow season in new ski pants.</p></li>
                <li><p><strong>FLEECE</strong><br>Do you need extra warmth while you&rsquo;re out on the trails? Layer up in a cozy fleece jacket. A fleece is great for thermal insulation, however it&rsquo;s not waterproof. Some fleece jackets offer windproof protection, like The North Face&rsquo;s Windwall<sup>&reg;</sup> technology. To keep the cold out, make sure your fleece has an adjustable hood and plenty of drawstrings. Warm up to a fresh fleece this winter!</p></li>
                <li><p><strong>GLOVES</strong><br>Hands down, gloves are a clutch part of your skiing or snowboarding gear. How do you keep your hands warm in sub-zero temperatures? To keep your hands toasty, make sure your gloves have a fleece lining, thermal insulation and adjustable tab closures to keep the cold out. You&rsquo;ll want to look for styles that are made of waterproof and breathable materials, like GORE-TEX<sup>&reg;</sup>. If you need to operate your phone without taking off your gloves, check out gloves that are compatible with touchscreens. Race into Macy&rsquo;s for ski gloves and other cold-weather accessories.</p></li>
                <li><p><strong>HATS</strong><br>Has your ski/snowboarding gear reached its peak? Top off your ski lineup with a cozy hat or headband. Check out styles with fleece to keep you warmer out on slopes. Are you worried about getting overheated? Ensure your hat has the latest breathable and quick-drying technologies to keep you comfy. Want a coordinated look? Score a hat that matches your gloves. From beanies to headbands, Macy&rsquo;s has the headwear you need to take your ski style to the summit this cold-weather season!</p></li>
